# Mimir project rules

Read [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) for the full project guide. The essentials:

- Run all tooling through `uv` (e.g. `uv run pytest`). Prefer `make` targets:
  `make fmt`, `make lint`, `make typecheck`, `make test`.
- Before finishing code changes, ensure `ruff check`, `black --check`,
  `mypy src`, and `pytest` all pass.
- Conventional commits (`feat`/`fix`/`chore`/`docs`/`refactor`/`test`/`ci`/`deps`)
  and branch names `<type>/<short-slug>`.
- `main` is protected (required checks + 1 review). Use the branch -> PR ->
  squash-merge flow; never force-push `main` or weaken protection.
- Never commit `.env`, `qdrant_storage/`, `notes/` contents, `site/`, or `.cache/`.
- Only commit when explicitly asked.
